          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":55,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"sunday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"26 km at easy pace (5:08-5:53/km). Keep effort conversational throughout. This mirrors your recent long run distance, so the goal is consistency, not extension.\"},\"monday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest. Recovery from Sunday is the work today.\"},\"tuesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"10 km easy (5:08-5:53/km). Flat or gently rolling terrain preferred. No pace pressure.\"},\"wednesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest or light walking. Keep legs fresh for Thursday.\"},\"thursday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"11 km total: 2 km easy warm-up, 6 km at threshold pace (4:16/km), 3 km easy cool-down. First threshold session of the block. Aim for steady, controlled effort, not a race effort.\"},\"friday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. Three runs this week is intentional given the prior low-volume week of 2026-02-23. Building back conservatively.\"},\"saturday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"8 km easy (5:08-5:53/km). Shake-out effort. Keep it genuinely easy.\"},\"week_summary\":\"Week 1 of the Base phase. Target is 55 km, a modest step down from your recent 60 km weeks. This is deliberate. The February dip to 10 km means your body has had mixed loading, and a controlled re-entry is lower risk than jumping straight to 60 km. Four run days are included this week. The structure is two easy runs bracketing a threshold session, with the long run anchoring Sunday. All runs cap well under 90 minutes at your paces. Threshold pace is drawn from your Daniels-Gilbert zones at 4:16/km. Marathon pace work begins in Week 2.\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
